    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Given $Z=80 x+120 y$, subject to constraints are $x+3 y \\leq 30 ; 3 x+4 y \\leq 60 ; x \\geq 0 ; y \\geq 0$.\nP is one of the corner points of the feasible region for the given Linear Programming Problem.\nThen the coordinate of $P$ is\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $(0,15)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $(20,0)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $(6,12)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $(30,0)$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let’s check which of the given points satisfies all the constraints</p>\n<p>$$ x+3y\\le30,\\quad 3x+4y\\le60,\\quad x\\ge0,\\quad y\\ge0. $$</p>\n\n<p><p>Option A: $(0,15)$  </p>\n<p>– $x+3y=0+45=45>30$ ✗</p></p>\n<p><p>Option B: $(20,0)$  </p>\n<p>– $x+3y=20+0=20\\le30$ ✓  </p>\n<p>– $3x+4y=60+0=60\\le60$ ✓</p></p>\n<p><p>Option C: $(6,12)$  </p>\n<p>– $x+3y=6+36=42>30$ ✗</p></p>\n<p><p>Option D: $(30,0)$  </p>\n<p>– $3x+4y=90>60$ ✗</p></p>\n\n<p>Only $(20,0)$ satisfies all constraints.  </p>\n<p>Answer: Option B, $(20,0)$.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2025-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "The corner points of the feasible region determined by the system of linear constraints are $(0,3),(1,1)$ and $(3,0)$, If objective function is $Z=p x+q y, p, q>0$ then the condition on $p$ and $q$ so that the minimum of $Z$ occurs at $(3,0)$ and $(1,1)$ is\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $p=3 q$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $3 p=q$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $p=\\frac{q}{2}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $p=2 q$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>First equate the objective at the two points:</p>\n\n<p>At (3, 0):  </p>\n\n<p>$$Z=3p.$$  </p>\n\n<p>At (1, 1):  </p>\n\n<p>$$Z=p+q.$$  </p>\n<p>For these to tie as the minimum,  </p>\n<p>$$3p = p + q\\;\\;\\Longrightarrow\\;\\;2p = q\\;\\;\\Longrightarrow\\;\\;p=\\frac q2.$$  </p>\n<p>Equivalently, the slope of the iso-cost line is  </p>\n<p>$$-\\frac p q = -\\frac12,$$  </p>\n<p>which matches the slope of the edge joining (3, 0) and (1, 1).  </p>\n<p>Hence the required condition is  </p>\n<p>Option C: $$p=\\frac q2\\,. $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2025-afternoon-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>For a given Linear Programming problem, the objective function is</p>\n<p>$$z=3 x+2 y$$</p>\n<p>Subject to constraints are</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& 4 x+3 y \\leq 60 \\\\\n& x \\geq 3 \\\\\n& y \\leq 2 x \\\\\n& y \\geq 0\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>P is one of the corner points of the feasible region for the given Linear Programming problem. Then the coordinate of P is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $(3,6)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $(0,20)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $(0,0)$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $(12,6)$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let’s find all vertices (corner points) by intersecting the active constraints:</p>\n\n<p><p>x = 3  and  y = 0  </p>\n<p>⇒ (3, 0)  </p></p>\n<p><p>x = 3  and  y = 2x  </p>\n<p>⇒ y = 2·3=6 ⇒ (3, 6)  </p></p>\n<p><p>y = 0  and  4x+3y=60  </p>\n<p>⇒ 4x=60 ⇒ x=15 ⇒ (15, 0)  </p></p>\n<p><p>y=2x  and  4x+3y=60  </p>\n<p>⇒ 4x+3(2x)=60 ⇒10x=60 ⇒ x=6,  y=12 ⇒ (6, 12)  </p></p>\n\n<p>Checking feasibility (x≥3, y≥0, y≤2x, 4x+3y≤60), all four are valid.  </p>\n<p>Among the given choices only (3, 6) appears, so</p>\n<p>Answer: (3, 6).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2025-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The maximum value of $$P=500 x+400 y$$ for the given constraints $$x+y \\leq 200, \\quad x \\geq 20, \\quad y \\geq 4 x, \\quad y \\geq 0$$ is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "96,000"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "84,000"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "98,000"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "82,000"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>To find the maximum value of $P = 500x + 400y$ subject to the given constraints, we first identify the feasible region defined by the constraints:</p>\n\n<p><p>$x + y \\leq 200$</p></p>\n<p><p>$x \\geq 20$</p></p>\n<p><p>$y \\geq 4x$</p></p>\n<p><p>$y \\geq 0$</p></p>\n\n<p>We find the vertices of the feasible region by determining the intersection points of the boundary lines:</p>\n\n<p><p>$x + y = 200$</p></p>\n<p><p>$x = 20$</p></p>\n<p><p>$y = 4x$</p></p>\n<p><p>$y = 0$</p></p>\n\n<p>Let's find the intersection points that satisfy all constraints:</p>\n<p>Intersection 1: $x = 20$ and $y = 4x$.</p>\n<p>Substitute $x=20$ into $y=4x$: $y = 4(20) = 80$.</p>\n<p>Point: $(20, 80)$.</p>\n<p>Check constraints: $20+80=100 \\leq 200$ (satisfied), $20 \\geq 20$ (satisfied), $80 \\geq 4(20)=80$ (satisfied), $80 \\geq 0$ (satisfied). This is a vertex.</p>\n<p>Intersection 2: $x = 20$ and $x + y = 200$.</p>\n<p>Substitute $x=20$ into $x+y=200$: $20 + y = 200 \\Rightarrow y = 180$.</p>\n<p>Point: $(20, 180)$.</p>\n<p>Check constraints: $20+180=200 \\leq 200$ (satisfied), $20 \\geq 20$ (satisfied), $180 \\geq 4(20)=80$ (satisfied), $180 \\geq 0$ (satisfied). This is a vertex.</p>\n<p>Intersection 3: $y = 4x$ and $x + y = 200$.</p>\n<p>Substitute $y=4x$ into $x+y=200$: $x + 4x = 200 \\Rightarrow 5x = 200 \\Rightarrow x = 40$.</p>\n<p>Then $y = 4(40) = 160$.</p>\n<p>Point: $(40, 160)$.</p>\n<p>Check constraints: $40+160=200 \\leq 200$ (satisfied), $40 \\geq 20$ (satisfied), $160 \\geq 4(40)=160$ (satisfied), $160 \\geq 0$ (satisfied). This is a vertex.</p>\n<p>The feasible region is a polygon with vertices at $(20, 80)$, $(20, 180)$, and $(40, 160)$.</p>\n<p>Now, we evaluate the objective function $P = 500x + 400y$ at each vertex:</p>\n<p>At $(20, 80)$:</p>\n<p>$P = 500(20) + 400(80) = 10000 + 32000 = 42000$.</p>\n<p>At $(20, 180)$:</p>\n<p>$P = 500(20) + 400(180) = 10000 + 72000 = 82000$.</p>\n<p>At $(40, 160)$:</p>\n<p>$P = 500(40) + 400(160) = 20000 + 64000 = 84000$.</p>\n<p>Comparing the values, the maximum value of $P$ is 84,000.</p>\n<p>The final answer is $\\boxed{84,000}$.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2024-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
