    "explanation": "<p>The given inequations are $$x+2 y \\geq 4,2 x+y \\leq 6, x, y \\leq 0$$.</p>\n<p>According to the inequtions $$x, y \\geq 0$$, the feasible region be the first quadrant (including positive $$\\mathrm{X}$$ and positive Y-axis). According to the inequation $$x+2 y \\geq 4$$, the feasible region be the region above or on the line $$x+2 y=4$$.</p>\n<p>According to the inequation $$2 x+y \\leq 6$$, the feasible region be the region below or on the line $$2 x+y=6$$. Now, the common feasible region will be the required feasible region.</p>\n<p>Thus, option (a) is correct.</p>",
