    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Feasible region ABCA and Z = 4x + 2y</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lito3ml9/23359d61-a741-4f33-989c-805eeb612e07/7d96bcd0-0992-11ee-a7a0-cd87ad84ee08/file-6y3zli1lito3mla.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lito3ml9/23359d61-a741-4f33-989c-805eeb612e07/7d96bcd0-0992-11ee-a7a0-cd87ad84ee08/file-6y3zli1lito3mla.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2022 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 14 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>At point C(9, 5), Z = 4 $$\\times$$ 9 + 2 $$\\times$$ 5 = 46</p>\n<p>At point A(11.5, 0), Z = 4 $$\\times$$ 11.5 + 2 $$\\times$$ 0 = 46</p>\n<p>At point B(24, 0), Z = 4 $$\\times$$ 24 + 0 = 96</p>\n<p>Hence, maximum value of Z is 96.</p>",
