    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, constraints are $$x\\ge0,y\\ge0,x+y\\ge5$$ and $$3x+y\\le9$$ and $$z=12x+3y$$</p>\n<p>Here, feasible region is OABCO.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lito4zzq/fa0693cd-74ae-4203-8975-c535691e4929/a3c02d60-0992-11ee-a7a0-cd87ad84ee08/file-6y3zli1lito4zzr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lito4zzq/fa0693cd-74ae-4203-8975-c535691e4929/a3c02d60-0992-11ee-a7a0-cd87ad84ee08/file-6y3zli1lito4zzr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2022 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 13 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>At point $$O(0,0),z=12(0)+3(0)=0$$</p>\n<p>At point $$A(3,0),z=12(3)+3(0)=36$$</p>\n<p>At point $$B(2,3),z=12(2)+3(3)=33$$</p>\n<p>At point $$C(0,5),z=12(0)+3(5)=15$$</p>\n<p>Hence, maximum value of z is 36.</p>",
