    "explanation": "<p>Consider the given inequation as $$2x+3y=6$$.</p>\n<p>Table for equation $$2x+3y=6$$ or $$y=\\frac{6-2x}{3}$$ is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lpzu4fk0/6b984a7b-8fce-4236-a388-ca2958a8650f/42499c00-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu4fk1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lpzu4fk0/6b984a7b-8fce-4236-a388-ca2958a8650f/42499c00-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu4fk1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 15 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>On putting (0, 0) in the inequality $$2x+3y\\le6$$, we get</p>\n<p>Consider $$x+y=2$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lpzu4cdf/8c92e037-01de-42aa-8351-de300abde870/3fd42f30-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu4cdg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lpzu4cdf/8c92e037-01de-42aa-8351-de300abde870/3fd42f30-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu4cdg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 15 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$0\\le6$$ which is true.</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow$$ Feasible region will be towards origin</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lpzu48r8/d79f453b-49bf-4c4d-b2e4-0e8620467450/3d090140-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu48r9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lpzu48r8/d79f453b-49bf-4c4d-b2e4-0e8620467450/3d090140-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu48r9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 15 English Explanation 3\"></p>",
