  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The maximum value of $$x+y$$ subject to $$2x+3y\\le6,x\\ge0,y\\ge0$$ is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "5"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "4"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "6"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "3"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let $$Z=x+y$$</p>\n<p>Given, constraints are $$2x+3y\\le6,x\\ge0,y\\ge0$$.</p>\n<p>These constraints consider as equation $$2x+3y=6$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lpzu5uao/17665165-964c-4224-b607-265a0d616253/697bca00-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu5uap.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lpzu5uao/17665165-964c-4224-b607-265a0d616253/697bca00-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu5uap.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 17 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>This equation intersect X and Y-axes at A(3, 0) and B(0, 2). On putting (0, 0) in the inequality $$2x+3y\\le6$$, we get $$2\\times0+3\\times0\\le6\\Rightarrow0\\le6$$ (which is true). So, the feasible region is towards the origin.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ The corner points of a feasible region are O(0, 0), A(3, 0) and B(0, 2).</p>\n<p>The value of Z on these corner points are given below</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-c3ow{border-color:inherit;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n.tg .tg-7btt{border-color:inherit;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 478px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 243px\">\n<col style=\"width: 235px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Corner points</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Value of $$\\mathrm{Z(Z=x+y)}$$</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$O(0,0)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=0+0=0$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$A(3,0)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=3+0=3$$ (maximum)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$B(0,2)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=0+2=2$$</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>Hence, maximum value of Z is 3.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
