    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The corner points of the feasible region are O(0, 0), A(4, 0) and B(0, 3).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lpzu7rwv/9d4dda24-d522-49bb-9f4a-29f565b4fcb5/9f42b9f0-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu7rww.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lpzu7rwv/9d4dda24-d522-49bb-9f4a-29f565b4fcb5/9f42b9f0-978c-11ee-87fd-851b7b40a2c6/file-6y3zli1lpzu7rww.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 16 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>The value of Z on these corner points are given below</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-c3ow{border-color:inherit;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n.tg .tg-7btt{border-color:inherit;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 478px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 243px\">\n<col style=\"width: 235px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Corner points</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Value of $$\\mathrm{Z(Z=x+y)}$$</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$O(0,0)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=0+0=0$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$A(4,0)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=4+0=4$$ (maximum)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$B(0,3)$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-c3ow\">$$Z=0+3=3$$</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>Hence, Z(max) is 4 at point $$x=4$$ and $$y=0$$.</p>",
